About
Discover Grand Canal Shoppes at The Venetian Resort, an enchanting shopping and dining destination in the heart of The Venetian Resort on the Las Vegas Strip. Stroll cobblestone walkways with illuminated, painted-sky ceilings, exploring award-winning flavors and signature shopping. Grand Canal Shoppes is also now home to exclusive, unique experiences sure to create lasting memories, such as KAMU Ultra Karaoke; Museum of Dream Space; and Madame Tussauds.
Duration: 1-2 hours

  • TravelingSoccerLoon
    Saint Paul, Minnesota6,326 contributions
    Expensive Shopping but Highlight is a Visit to St Mark's Square
    The Grand Canal Shoppes at the Venetian is an upscale shopping mall filled with expensive stores. It is worth a look as you make your way to the re-creation of St Mark's Square. This re-creation which includes gondolas on canals is quite remarkable and very beautiful. You really feel like you're outdoors. It is Vegas kitsch at its very best. Gondola rides are available but, in my opinion, not worth it at $39 per person for a 10-minute ride. A gondola ride in the real Venice would be a bucket list item but not so much here. I think you can enjoy the experience of visiting the Venetian by just strolling about, grabbing a gelato, doing some window shopping and watching the gondolas and any entertainment that is offered. Beware that this area can get mobbed with people so I would suggest visiting early in the day before the crowds build. It is also extremely difficult to find your way to the square and more importantly, how to find your way out. It is quite a maze and not well marked which I suspect is intentional as it keeps you trapped longer.
    Visited June 2023
    Traveled with friends
